<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,591,617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[333,433,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Kupiuka" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Kupiuka</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
differs from the remaining genera of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Heliophaninae">Heliophaninae</taxonomicName>
by having the glandular portion of the wall of the copulation duct developed into what appears to be an extra spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[1217,1292,629,655]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,271,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[155,1424,389,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,381,1878]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Kupiuka extratheca sp. nov. 1 male habitus; 2 – 3 left male palp, (2 ventral, 3 retrolateral); 4 – 5 male palpal femur (4 retrolateral, 5 prolateral); 6 epigyne, ventral view; 7 vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.25 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1305,1336,629,655]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1491,1515]" captionTargetBox="[166,1428,1004,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,943,1470]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 16. Kupiuka taruman sp. nov. 15 epigyne, ventral view; 16 vulva, dorsal view. Scale: 0.25 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="58">16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1349,1382,629,655]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 22" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[162,1432,26,1134]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,194,1146]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 22. Kupiuka heteropicta sp. nov. 17 – 19 left male palp (17 ventral, 18 retrolateral, 19 ventroretrolateral); 20 male palpal femur, prolateral view; 21 epigyne, ventral view; 22 vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.25 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="58">22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,356,666,692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Description.</emphasis>
The genus includes small jumping spiders (2–4mm) with granulose areas on the lateral surfaces of the anterior carapace and three modified setae on the distal prolateral portion of femur I for stridulation, as those described for species of 
<emphasis box="[680,779,741,767]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Helvetia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[835,949,741,767]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Matagaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Matagaia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(see Ruiz &amp; Brescovit 2008, figs 2–3 and Ruiz 
<emphasis box="[214,266,778,804]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">et al</emphasis>
. 2007, figs 1–2); bodies are slightly elongate and flattened; chelicerae with two teeth on promargin and one on retromargin; male palps with a prolateral depression on femora; glandular portion of the wall of the copulation duct of the epigyne seems to be developed into an extra spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[1135,1210,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,271,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[155,1424,389,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,381,1878]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Kupiuka extratheca sp. nov. 1 male habitus; 2 – 3 left male palp, (2 ventral, 3 retrolateral); 4 – 5 male palpal femur (4 retrolateral, 5 prolateral); 6 epigyne, ventral view; 7 vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.25 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1222,1253,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1491,1515]" captionTargetBox="[166,1428,1004,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,943,1470]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 16. Kupiuka taruman sp. nov. 15 epigyne, ventral view; 16 vulva, dorsal view. Scale: 0.25 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="58">16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1265,1298,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 22" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[162,1432,26,1134]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,194,1146]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 22. Kupiuka heteropicta sp. nov. 17 – 19 left male palp (17 ventral, 18 retrolateral, 19 ventroretrolateral); 20 male palpal femur, prolateral view; 21 epigyne, ventral view; 22 vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.25 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="58">22</figureCitation>
), while true spermathecae are not differentiated in girth. This apparent extra spermatheca is probably homologous to the flower-shaped gland present in dendryphantines (see Maddison 1996: 225, fig. 5) and long, chimney-like structures (also treated by some authors as “scent gland”, e.g. Berry &amp; Prószyński 2001) present in other salticids, such as amycines and sitticines (Amycoida) or even in 
<taxonomicName authority="Berry &amp; Prószyński, 2001" authorityName="Berry &amp; Prószyński" authorityYear="2001" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hakka" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[979,1060,1002,1028]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Hakka</emphasis>
Berry &amp; Prószyński, 2001
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1902" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pseudicius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,278,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Pseudicius</emphasis>
Simon, 1902
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Heliophaninae">Heliophaninae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
